The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) said yesterday it has put in place necessary facilities and infrastructure to ensure seamless movement of passengers during the Eid-el-fitri celebration.  Spokesperson of the authority, Mrs. Henrietta Yakubu said assured all airport users that her network of airports across the country are fully ready for the upsurge of passengers during the festival.  The authority also reiterated the recently implemented cashless policy at the airports, advising that all payments due to the agency should be done electronically. yakubu said: “In line with our core mandate of ensuring seamless facilitation of air travellers, FAAN has put in place all necessary facilities and infrastructure to ensure safe passage and a delightful experience at all airports in Nigeria.

“We advise all our esteemed passengers and airport users to always get to the airports early enough as we envisage a surge in traffic. This will enable them to complete their check-in formalities in good time and prevent the embarassment of missing flights, we will also like to remind all airport users that our airports are now cashless as all payments to the Authority should now be done electronically”.